{
  "stem": "1282.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not only being freed by the Americans, not only getting out of the camps, but surviving thereafter was very, very difficult.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And whether my beliefs in the Jewish faith was shaken-- not as a Jew, but as a religion I have questioned myself many times.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If it's a just God, how he could he stand by?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I'd like to believe that he's a merciful and he's a just God.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yes, it was very painful for me to accept God in the way I have accepted him, unquestionably when I was a child.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't question it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I believed in it the way I was taught.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After the Holocaust, I did not alienate the belief in God, but it was a very, very torturous, very difficult to continually believe in the same faith, with the same faith, with the same impact in God.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Eventually, I have compromised.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I still believe in God, but I'm not as dedicated as a Jew as I was.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm dedicated to Judaism, but not the religion as much as someone would want me to.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I participate as a Jew in everything that is Jewish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Judaism is-- the religious-- I separate the religion from the morality and the spirituality of being a Jew.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I live a Jewish life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I attend all Jewish activities.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I get myself involved in Jewish charitable work.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I believe in the promotion of the Jewish faith, raising children to understand the Jewish faith.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I'm not dedicated to the temple.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I attend temple two, three times a year.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I am-- what I have been for years, a member of the Board of Directors at Sinai Temple, which is the largest conservative synagogue.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
